Multiple Choice Question Why were the triumphant Communists of Russia hostile to the Allied Powers? The new leaders did not have a strong grip on Russia and felt threatened by the Allied Powers. Russia had never supported the Allied effort to win World War I. The Communists feared that the Russian people would welcome an Allied takeover of the country. The Allied Powers had helped the enemies of the Communists.
